//Demografia
Population Data In 2013, the municipality of Valledupar has a population, according to official projections DANE, 3 433 242 inhabitants, of whom 368,674 live in the village, the rest, about 64,327 are distributed among the 25 districts that make up the municipality. Distribution Of the total population, 52.1 are women, 12.2 calls itself raizal, black, palenquero, black, or African American. 88.3 of over 5 years literate, the enrollment rate between 5 and 18 years of age is 80.
